# 🧠 OS Concept 1: Chaos Engineering Basics

🔥 Modern reliability engineering concept.

---

## 1️⃣ Simple Idea

Instead of waiting for failures:

👉 intentionally create failures to test system resilience.

---

## 🧠 Real-World Analogy

Fire drill 🚨

Practice failure before real emergency happens.

---

## Examples

* shutting down servers
* simulating network failure
* database slowdown testing

---

## Why Important?

Helps verify:

✔ fault tolerance
✔ recovery mechanisms
✔ system stability

---

## Famous Example

* Netflix Chaos Monkey

---

## 🎯 Placement Question

**Q: Why chaos engineering useful?**

👉 It helps identify weaknesses before real failures occur.

---

## 🧠 Memory Trick

```text id="x4m8qp"
Create failures safely to improve reliability
```

